We weren't acting in bad
faith, we just basically

01:04:01.400 --> 01:04:05.639
didn't think we'd lose and
so we didn't bother to do it,

01:04:05.639 --> 01:04:06.680
so now we want a do-over.

01:04:10.350 --> 01:04:12.175
And in this do-over,
we're not only

01:04:12.175 --> 01:04:14.800
going to rely on our new policy,
which is the same policy, just

01:04:14.800 --> 01:04:18.200
tweaked a little, but
we're also beyond just 7E,

01:04:18.200 --> 01:04:20.510
which we're using in the
new policy, just tweaked.

01:04:20.510 --> 01:04:24.210
We're also going to bring in
exemptions 1, 3, 5, 6, 7A, 7C,

01:04:24.210 --> 01:04:25.430
7D, and 7F.

01:04:28.620 --> 01:04:30.400
This case actually
warrants its own talk.

01:04:30.400 --> 01:04:32.500
It just goes on forever.

01:04:32.500 --> 01:04:37.151
But the judge, while pissed at
the FBI for obvious reasons,

01:04:37.151 --> 01:04:38.900
essentially gave the
FBI almost everything

01:04:38.900 --> 01:04:40.691
they wanted, because
at the end of the day,

01:04:40.691 --> 01:04:45.010
even judges who are
skeptical, end up

01:04:45.010 --> 01:04:49.147
balking too much of the time and
the FBI turns around and says,

01:04:49.147 --> 01:04:49.730
really, judge?

01:04:49.730 --> 01:04:50.030
Really?

01:04:50.030 --> 01:04:52.090
You know national security
better than the FBI?

01:04:52.090 --> 01:04:54.048
Oh, where'd you go to
national security school?

01:04:54.048 --> 01:04:57.110
Because we're the FBI and I know
it doesn't seem like a big deal

01:04:57.110 --> 01:04:59.330
to you, but do you want
the next twin towers

01:04:59.330 --> 01:05:00.500
falling on your hands?

01:05:00.500 --> 01:05:01.400
Because that's what
it's going to be

01:05:01.400 --> 01:05:02.941
and we're going to
make sure everyone

01:05:02.941 --> 01:05:04.540
knows it when you
cause it to happen.

01:05:04.540 --> 01:05:06.540
So you want to release
records on puppy huggers?

01:05:06.540 --> 01:05:08.123
You want to release
FOIA search slips?

01:05:08.123 --> 01:05:10.871
You think you know national
security better than the FBI?

01:05:10.871 --> 01:05:12.620
We're going to make
sure everyone knows it

01:05:12.620 --> 01:05:14.310
when people die on your watch.

01:05:14.310 --> 01:05:17.630
And the judges, far
more often than is

01:05:17.630 --> 01:05:26.330
acceptable in a democracy, they
cave and defer to the agency.

01:05:26.330 --> 01:05:28.080
So when the FBI screams
national security,

01:05:28.080 --> 01:05:30.705
even for FOIA search slips-- and
that's what exemptions 1 and 3

01:05:30.705 --> 01:05:32.660
are about here--

01:05:32.660 --> 01:05:33.350
judges cave.

01:05:33.350 --> 01:05:36.750
And this case is ongoing
and we're still fighting it.

01:05:36.750 --> 01:05:39.349
But again, remember, all of
this happening in this case

01:05:39.349 --> 01:05:41.640
is occurring primarily just
so that the FBI can prevent

01:05:41.640 --> 01:05:44.730
FOIA requesters from seeing how
deliberatively shitty FBI FOIA

01:05:44.730 --> 01:05:47.235
searches actually are.

01:05:47.235 --> 01:05:49.860
So, as I said, FOIA's one of the
most underappreciated elements

01:05:49.860 --> 01:05:50.970
of the entire
American experiment.

01:05:50.970 --> 01:05:52.080
The notion that the
records of government

01:05:52.080 --> 01:05:53.100
are the property of
the people and all

01:05:53.100 --> 01:05:55.475
we need to do to get them is
to ask for them is radically

01:05:55.475 --> 01:05:56.804
democratic but FOIA is broken.

01:05:56.804 --> 01:05:59.220
And this is just one part of
the ongoing crisis of secrecy

01:05:59.220 --> 01:06:01.311
we now face.

01:06:01.311 --> 01:06:05.280
A Harvard historian of
science, Peter Gallison,

01:06:05.280 --> 01:06:08.521
has shown that the universe
of classified knowledge--

01:06:08.521 --> 01:06:10.020
published classified
knowledge-- now

01:06:10.020 --> 01:06:12.660
exponentially exceeds
the universe of published

01:06:12.660 --> 01:06:13.860
unclassified knowledge.

01:06:13.860 --> 01:06:16.140
And this disparity
grows worse by the day.

01:06:16.140 --> 01:06:19.110
Literally, the
universe of published

01:06:19.110 --> 01:06:22.380
unclassified knowledge
is dwarfed exponentially

01:06:22.380 --> 01:06:23.599
by classified knowledge.

01:06:23.599 --> 01:06:25.890
The vast majority of published
information in the world

01:06:25.890 --> 01:06:29.855
is inaccessible without
security clearances.

01:06:29.855 --> 01:06:31.980
And classification is just
one part of the problem.

01:06:31.980 --> 01:06:33.813
Most of the records I'm
seeking from the FBI

01:06:33.813 --> 01:06:35.115
here aren't classified.

01:06:35.115 --> 01:06:36.740
The government just
won't give them up.

01:06:36.740 --> 01:06:39.580
In fact, the FBI and DOJ invoke
classification only about 5%

01:06:39.580 --> 01:06:41.470
of the times when it
denies FOIA requests.

01:06:41.470 --> 01:06:44.230
95% of FOIA denials are not
pertaining to classified,

01:06:44.230 --> 01:06:45.970
they just deny them
for whatever reasons.

01:06:45.970 --> 01:06:48.553
7E is not classified, it's just
law enforcement techniques not

01:06:48.553 --> 01:06:51.090
generally known to the public.

01:06:51.090 --> 01:06:55.780
Secrecy is a cancer on
the body of democracy.

01:06:55.780 --> 01:06:58.750
And you know,
increasingly, my focus

01:06:58.750 --> 01:07:01.240
